    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Titus",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 2,
        "summary": "Saints should live righteously, deny ungodliness, and seek the Lord.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "But speak thou the things which become sound doctrine:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Thes. 2:4; 1\u00a0Pet. 4:11. TG\u00a0Teaching.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 9
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 88:77 (77\u201378).",
                        "start": 45,
                        "end": 53
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "That the aged men be sober, grave, temperate, sound in faith, in charity, in patience.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Old Age.",
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 13
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0circumspect.",
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 26
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Temperance.",
                        "start": 35,
                        "end": 44
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The aged women likewise, that they be in behaviour as becometh holiness, not false accusers, not given to much wine, teachers of good things;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0slanderers, traitors, devils.",
                        "start": 77,
                        "end": 82
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Gossip.",
                        "start": 83,
                        "end": 91
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 37
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "That they may teach the young women to be sober, to love their husbands, to love their children,",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Marriage, Wives.",
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 35
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Family, Love within.",
                        "start": 52,
                        "end": 56
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "To be discreet, chaste, keepers at home, good, obedient to their own husbands, that the word of God be not blasphemed.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Chastity; Modesty.",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 22
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0housekeepers, guards.",
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 31
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Tim. 5:14.",
                        "start": 35,
                        "end": 39
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 5
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Young men likewise exhort to be sober minded.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "In all things shewing thyself a pattern of good works: in doctrine shewing uncorruptness, gravity, sincerity,",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0dignity, respectfulness.",
                        "start": 90,
                        "end": 97
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sincere.",
                        "start": 99,
                        "end": 108
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 74
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Sound speech, that cannot be condemned; that he that is of the contrary part may be ashamed, having no evil thing to say of you.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Tim. 6:3.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 5
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Pet. 2:12 (11\u201312).",
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 38
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0an opponent, enemy.",
                        "start": 56,
                        "end": 76
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Exhort servants to be obedient unto their own masters, and to please them well in all things; not answering again;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Eph. 6:5; Col. 3:22; 1\u00a0Tim. 6:1 (1\u20132); 1\u00a0Pet. 2:18.",
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 15
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0arguing against, opposing, contradicting.",
                        "start": 98,
                        "end": 113
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 6
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 55,
                        "end": 58
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 73
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 86,
                        "end": 93
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Not purloining, but shewing all good fidelity; that they may adorn the doctrine of God our Saviour in all things.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0misappropriating, robbing. TG\u00a0Stealing.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 14
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0honor, put in order.",
                        "start": 61,
                        "end": 66
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For the grace of God that bringeth salvation hath appeared to all men,",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Grace.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 13
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a0Titus 2:11 \u2026 which bringeth salvation to all men, hath appeared;",
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 25
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Teaching us that, denying ungodliness and worldly lusts, we should live soberly, righteously, and godly, in this present world;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Godliness.",
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 37
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Worldliness.",
                        "start": 42,
                        "end": 49
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Lust.",
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 55
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Levity.",
                        "start": 72,
                        "end": 79
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Abundant Life; Righteousness.",
                        "start": 81,
                        "end": 92
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Looking for that blessed hope, and the glorious appearing of the great God and our Saviour Jesus Christ;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Glory.",
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 47
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Who gave himself for us, that he might redeem us from all iniquity, and purify unto himself a peculiar people, zealous of good works.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Self-Sacrifice.",
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Atonement through; Jesus Christ, Redeemer; Redemption.",
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 45
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Purification; Purity.",
                        "start": 72,
                        "end": 78
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Peculiar People.",
                        "start": 94,
                        "end": 109
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Zeal.",
                        "start": 111,
                        "end": 118
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "These things speak, and exhort, and rebuke with all authority. Let no man despise thee.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Chastening.",
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 42
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Authority.",
                        "start": 52,
                        "end": 61
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0disregard.",
                        "start": 74,
                        "end": 81
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
}